---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StepCard from '../../components/StepCard.astro';
---

<Layout title="Install OpenClaw" lang="en" currentPath="/guide/install" description="Step-by-step guide to installing OpenClaw on macOS, Linux, or Windows.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge badge-orange">Installation Guide</span>
      <h1>Install OpenClaw</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Get your self-hosted AI gateway running in under 5 minutes. Works on macOS, Linux, and Windows (WSL2).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <aside class="toc">
          <div class="toc-inner">
            <div class="toc-title">On This Page</div>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#what-is-openclaw">What is OpenClaw?</a></li>
              <li><a href="#requirements">System Requirements</a></li>
              <li><a href="#install-steps">Installation Steps</a></li>
              <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <article class="article">
          <!-- What is OpenClaw -->
          <section id="what-is-openclaw" class="article-section">
            <h2>What is OpenClaw?</h2>
            <p>
              OpenClaw is a <strong>self-hosted AI gateway</strong> ‚Äî a Node.js process you run on your own machine or server
              that acts as the brain connecting your chat apps (Telegram, WhatsApp, Discord, iMessage) to AI agents powered by
              models like Claude, GPT-4, or any OpenAI-compatible API. Instead of paying for multiple AI chatbot subscriptions
              that don't know each other, you run one gateway that serves all your channels simultaneously.
            </p>
            <p>
              The key insight: your AI assistant should be reachable from wherever you are, on whatever device you have.
              OpenClaw makes that possible without surrendering your data to a third-party cloud service.
            </p>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-icon">üí°</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Open Source & MIT Licensed</strong> ‚Äî The full source code is available on GitHub.
                You can inspect it, modify it, and contribute back to the community.
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Requirements -->
          <section id="requirements" class="article-section">
            <h2>System Requirements</h2>
            <div class="requirements-grid">
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üü¢</div>
                <div class="req-label">Node.js</div>
                <div class="req-value">v22 or later</div>
                <div class="req-note">Use <code>node --version</code> to check</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üîë</div>
                <div class="req-label">API Key</div>
                <div class="req-value">Anthropic recommended</div>
                <div class="req-note">OpenAI-compatible APIs also work</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üíª</div>
                <div class="req-label">OS</div>
                <div class="req-value">macOS / Linux / WSL2</div>
                <div class="req-note">Native Windows via WSL2</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üåê</div>
                <div class="req-label">npm</div>
                <div class="req-value">Bundled with Node.js</div>
                <div class="req-note">v9+ recommended</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>
              Don't have Node.js 22? Install it via <a href="https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm" target="_blank">nvm</a>:
            </p>
            <pre><code>curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
nvm install 22
nvm use 22</code></pre>
          </section>

          <!-- Install Steps -->
          <section id="install-steps" class="article-section">
            <h2>Installation Steps</h2>

            <StepCard number={1} title="Install OpenClaw globally">
              <pre><code>npm install -g openclaw@latest</code></pre>
              <p>This installs the <code>openclaw</code> CLI globally. After it completes, verify with:</p>
              <pre><code>openclaw --version</code></pre>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={2} title="Run the onboarding wizard">
              <pre><code>openclaw onboard --install-daemon</code></pre>
              <p>The wizard will ask you to:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Choose your AI provider (Anthropic / OpenAI / OpenRouter)</li>
                <li>Enter your API key</li>
                <li>Set a workspace directory (default: <code>~/.openclaw/workspace</code>)</li>
                <li>Install the background daemon service (so OpenClaw starts on boot)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="tip-box">
                <strong>üí° Tip:</strong> Get an Anthropic API key at <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank">console.anthropic.com</a>.
                New accounts get $5 free credits ‚Äî more than enough to get started.
              </div>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={3} title="Connect your first channel">
              <pre><code>openclaw channels login</code></pre>
              <p>
                This opens an interactive menu to connect WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, or other supported channels.
                For Telegram, you'll need a bot token ‚Äî see the <a href="/guide/telegram">Telegram guide</a> for details.
              </p>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={4} title="Start the Gateway">
              <pre><code>openclaw gateway --port 18789</code></pre>
              <p>The gateway starts and prints the local dashboard URL:</p>
              <pre><code>‚úî Gateway running at http://127.0.0.1:18789/
‚úî Telegram: connected
‚úî Agent: Pi (Claude 3.5 Sonnet)</code></pre>
              <p>Open <code>http://127.0.0.1:18789/</code> in your browser to see the Control UI.</p>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={5} title="Send your first message">
              <p>
                Go to your connected chat app (Telegram, WhatsApp, etc.) and send a message.
                Your AI should respond within a few seconds. Try saying:
              </p>
              <pre><code>Hello! What can you do for me?</code></pre>
              <div class="success-box">
                <strong>‚úÖ You're live!</strong> If you get a response, your OpenClaw gateway is working perfectly.
              </div>
            </StepCard>
          </section>

          <!-- FAQ -->
          <section id="faq" class="article-section">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>

            <div class="faq-list">
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Does OpenClaw work on Windows without WSL?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>
                    OpenClaw requires a Unix-like environment. On Windows, you'll need WSL2 (Windows Subsystem for Linux).
                    Install WSL2 by running <code>wsl --install</code> in an admin PowerShell, then install Node.js inside your WSL environment.
                    The experience is identical to Linux once WSL2 is set up.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Which AI provider should I use?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>
                    <strong>Anthropic (Claude)</strong> is recommended for the best experience ‚Äî Claude models are particularly good
                    at following complex system prompts, using tools, and maintaining context. Claude 3.5 Sonnet offers an excellent
                    balance of capability and cost. That said, OpenClaw also works with OpenAI GPT-4o, and any OpenRouter model.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  What's the difference between the daemon and manually running the gateway?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>
                    The <strong>daemon</strong> (installed via <code>--install-daemon</code>) registers OpenClaw as a system service
                    that starts automatically on boot and restarts if it crashes. Manually running <code>openclaw gateway</code> works
                    fine for testing but stops when you close the terminal. For production use (24/7 availability), always use the daemon.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Can I run OpenClaw on a VPS or cloud server?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>
                    Absolutely ‚Äî this is a great setup. A $5‚Äì10/month VPS (DigitalOcean, Hetzner, Linode) running Ubuntu works perfectly.
                    The daemon approach is especially useful here. For remote access to the Control UI, OpenClaw supports Tailscale integration
                    to expose the dashboard securely without opening ports.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  How do I update OpenClaw?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>
                    Run the same install command to get the latest version:
                  </p>
                  <pre><code>npm install -g openclaw@latest</code></pre>
                  <p>Then restart the daemon:</p>
                  <pre><code>openclaw gateway restart</code></pre>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <div class="nav-buttons">
            <span></span>
            <a href="/guide/telegram" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Connect Telegram ‚Üí</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,107,53,0.08) 0%, transparent 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero .badge { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .page-content { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; }

  .toc-inner {
    position: sticky;
    top: 84px;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }
  .toc-title { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text2); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .toc ul { list-style: none; }
  .toc li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .toc a { color: var(--text2); font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .toc a:hover { color: var(--accent); opacity: 1; }

  .article-section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }
  .article-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .article-section p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .article-section ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem; }
  .article-section ul li { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text2); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .article-section ul li::before { content: "‚Üí"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--accent); }
  .article-section pre { margin: 1rem 0; }

  .info-box, .tip-box, .success-box {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .info-box { background: rgba(0,212,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(0,212,255,0.2); color: var(--text2); }
  .info-icon { font-size: 1.1rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.1rem; }
  .tip-box { background: rgba(255,107,53,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,53,0.2); color: var(--text2); }
  .success-box { background: rgba(0,200,100,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(0,200,100,0.2); color: var(--text2); }

  .requirements-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .req-card {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .req-icon { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .req-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text2); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .req-value { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .req-note { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text2); }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 1rem; }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .toc { display: none; }
    .requirements-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .requirements-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
